---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use - WattCostGuide"
  description="Terms of use for WattCostGuide appliance electricity cost calculators, educational guides, estimates, limitations, and external links."
>
  <section class="page-header">
    <h1>Terms</h1>
    <p>Electricity cost estimates are for general informational use and may differ from actual bills.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>Use of the site</h2>
    <p>
      WattCostGuide provides appliance electricity cost calculators, wattage ranges, and educational guides.
      You may use the site for personal research, household planning, and general cost comparisons.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>No utility billing advice</h2>
    <p>
      Results are estimates based on the watts, hours, and electricity rate entered. Actual costs can vary
      because of appliance efficiency, cycling behavior, weather, utility fees, taxes, demand charges, and
      time-of-use pricing.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>Content accuracy</h2>
    <p>
      We aim to keep examples practical and understandable, but wattage ranges are not a substitute for a
      product label, owner manual, utility bill, or professional energy audit.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>No professional advice</h2>
    <p>
      The site is provided for general educational use. It is not utility billing advice, engineering advice,
      financial advice, or a guarantee of savings. Before making major purchases or home energy changes, use
      product documentation, utility information, and qualified professional guidance where appropriate.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>External links and third parties</h2>
    <p>
      WattCostGuide may link to external resources such as utility information, manufacturer materials, or
      privacy and advertising resources. External sites are controlled by their own owners and may change
      without notice.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>Changes to these terms</h2>
    <p>
      These terms may be updated as the site adds content, calculators, advertising, analytics, or other
      features. Continued use of the site means you accept the current version posted here.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
